title: Christ Is Enough
theological_summary: This song centers Christian identity in the finished work and sufficiency of Christ. It frames discipleship as wholehearted trust rather than self-reliance. It is useful for reaffirming commitment after teaching on maturity, perseverance, or gospel-centered living.
arrangement_notes: Start acoustic with light pad, add drums in second half, and end with a gentle down dynamic for prayer.
notes_markdown: Works well in lower key for mixed congregation range. Keep intro concise and avoid long instrumental loops.
pastoral_use_markdown: Useful after messages on spiritual formation, baptism Sundays, or recommitment moments. Pairs naturally with prayers of surrender and commissioning.
